Tim's example is probably a bit overkill for your requirement. ¬†As I read it you just want a list of usernames, so this would probably do: 
```text
<?php
require_once('../config.php');
$results = $DB->get_records_menu('user', null, 'username asc', 'id, username');
echo '<pre>';
foreach ($results as $id => $username) {
  echo "$username\n";
}
echo '</pre>';
```
 Moodle's Data Manipulation API has done most of the heavy lifting for you. https://docs.moodle.org/dev/Data_manipulation_API The arguments passed to moodle_database::get_records_menu are: the table you want to query ('user'); any predicates for your query (null, because you want them all); the column by, and order in which, you want the results sorted; and the columns you want from the database The rest is ordinary PHP for looping through an associative array Hope this helps, Chris

